4. Behaviour of drivers yielding
right of way
Drivers who have to yield the right
of way shall not proceed until they
can do so without danger to other
vehicles, having regard to the posi-
tion, distance and speed of such
vehicles.
53. Special rule
When traffic is halted at an inter-
section, drivers may not stop their
vehicles in such a position as to pre-
vent the passage of other drivers
moving along the transverse road.
CHAPTER V. BEHAVIOUR OF
DRIVERS AT PEDESTRIAN

ance with paragraph 2 (1) of

(2) a vehicle may not overtake

ing;
